locality: Middle and upper slopes of the Pico das Almas, ca. 25km WNW of the Vila do Rio de Contas.
occurrenceRemarks: Tree to 3m. Leaves coriaceous dark glossy green above, bright rusty brown beneath. Inflorescence axis and calyces bright rusty brown to grey. Buds only.
name: Myrcia mischophylla Kiaersk.
habitat: Sandstone conglomerate metamorphic and quartzite rock outcrop with associated and scrubby vegetation with damp flushes, grassland and marsh in some areas. This plant is growing in 'Campo do Queroz' in mata de cigo woodland.

locality: On road to Abaira ca. 8km to N of the town of Rio de Contas.
